Aim

To analyze and represent an AI problem using PEAS (Performance, Environment, Actuators, Sensors) and identify suitable agent architecture.

Theory (Short & Viva-ready)
PEAS stands for:
Performance Measure → How success is measured
Environment → Where agent operates
Actuators → Outputs/actions
Sensors → Inputs from environment
Used to define task environment of intelligent agent
Example in your file: Smartwatch / Automated Car
Procedure
Select an AI problem (e.g., Smartwatch / Self-driving car)
Identify:
Performance Measures
Environment
Actuators
Sensors
Represent all in structured format
Decide suitable agent type (simple reflex, model-based, goal-based, etc.)
Diagram (Important for marks)

Draw this basic agent structure:

Environment → Sensors → Agent → Actuators → Environment

Label properly:

Input = Sensors
Output = Actuators
Example (Write in record if needed)
Smartwatch PEAS:
Performance → accuracy, battery life
Environment → human + surroundings
Actuators → display, vibration
Sensors → heart rate, GPS, accelerometer
